message: “It’s said that these are victimless crimes,” Williamson said. “But as you can see, there are victims all the way through. I think I can speak for all the law enforcement here when I say we will not ignore these issues.”

data.description: LAKE HAVASU CITY — Last week’s strike against an alleged human trafficking operation was an example of citizens helping law enforcement protect their communities, local and federal officials said Tuesday
data.title: Eight arrested in connection with massage parlors raid
